{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"20a530c3-dac8-4f8e-8691-43386bbe0f7b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string will appear in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"59198040-fa93-4834-8698-3889811bd149","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test skip/ignore attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"1BCB:1521A3:6BF0E50:7479336:6A03D27B"},"id":"1ab12c94-7a36-4af8-8a36-e82d0deb5dc0","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:23:15.275Z","parentId":"07668954-c14c-454c-8c10-21394cccca1f"}
